      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Agents: add claude-sdk runtime with native-tool bridge + Phase 3 default flip",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds an opt-in `claude-sdk` agent runtime driver backed by `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk`, alongside the existing `embedded` (pi-ai) and `acp` drivers, and flips the default to `claude-sdk` (Phase 3).\n\nThis is a re-submission of the original #68135 work, rebased onto current `main` (2420+ upstream commits of drift) with review-feedback fixes included.\n\n- **Runtime dispatch** — `src/agents/runtime-dispatch.ts` + `src/agents/claude-sdk/*` introduces the `runAgent` entry point that picks the active driver from `agents.list[<id>].runtime.type`. Default flips to `claude-sdk`; `embedded` kept explicit for the compat window.\n- **Native-tool bridge** — in-process MCP server exposes OpenClaw-native tools (`message`, `sessions.send`, `cron.add`, plugin-contributed) to the SDK via TypeBox→Zod schema conversion (`src/agents/claude-sdk/typebox-to-zod.ts` + `tools-adapter.ts`).\n- **Hooks adapter** — translates OpenClaw hook events to SDK equivalents; honors `HookInvocationPolicy.enabled` to skip disabled hooks (parity with embedded runtime).\n- **Credential modes** — `credential: \"subscription\" | \"profile\"` knob defaults to `subscription` so requests use the user's Claude.ai login rather than a metered API key.\n- **Session-mirror** — writes SDK turns to a sidecar file so pi-ai SessionManager's truncation race doesn't clobber our transcript.\n- **Tool-deny enforcement** — `tools.deny` + `tools.byProvider.anthropic.deny` now scope SDK built-ins (Bash, Read, Edit, Grep, Glob) via the SDK's `disallowedTools` option (matches how embedded filters native tools).\n\n## Plugin SDK surface\n\n- `runAgent` export from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/agent-runtime` for stable runtime-driver dispatch\n- `RunAgentResult` / `RunAgentParams` types exported from the same surface\n- Legacy `runEmbeddedPiAgent` export marked `@deprecated`; new plugins should migrate to `runAgent`\n\n## Skill → sub-agent generator\n\nEvery `skills/*/SKILL.md` and `.agents/skills/*/SKILL.md` now has a generated Claude Code sub-agent under `.claude/agents/<name>.md`; run `pnpm skills:subagents:gen` to regenerate and `pnpm skills:subagents:check` to gate drift.\n\n## Gates checked locally\n\n- `pnpm install` ✅\n- `pnpm plugin-sdk:api:check` ✅\n- `pnpm lint` ✅ (3 cherry-pick-era lint issues fixed in the last commit)\n\n## Rebase notes\n\n- Cherry-picked the 17 claude-sdk commits from the original #68135 branch onto current `origin/main` in chronological order.\n- `src/hooks/llm-slug-generator.ts` — kept upstream's `resolveAgentTimeoutMs` import AND added the claude-sdk commit's `runAgent` import.\n- `src/agents/command/attempt-execution.ts` — kept both `runEmbeddedPiAgent` type import (for `EmbeddedPiRunResult`) and new `runAgent` function import.\n- `src/agents/subagent-registry.ts` — kept upstream's `sweepInProgress` reentrancy guard.\n- `src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-memory.ts` — took upstream's lazy-loaded pi-embedded pattern; follow-up work can migrate memory flush to `runAgent`.\n- `docs/plugins/sdk-runtime.md` — kept upstream's doc phrasing; doc refresh can be a follow-up.\n- `CHANGELOG.md`, `pnpm-lock.yaml`, `docs/.generated/config-baseline.sha256`, `plugin-sdk-api-baseline.sha256` — kept upstream versions; baseline hashes regenerate on next check run.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] Lint green\n- [x] Plugin SDK API baseline check green\n- [ ] CI green (awaiting CI run on the PR)\n- [ ] Live smoke: `openclaw agent --runtime claude-sdk -p \"hello\"` produces the expected turn\n\n## Related\n\n- Closes #68135 (this is a re-submission with review feedback included)\n- Companion PR: #68936 (PR autofix pipeline) — independent, does not block this\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
        "branch": "feat/claude-sdk-runtime",
